                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13292653" author="hustlmsp" created="Mon, 11 Jun 2012 06:56:06 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;attach a patch to improve hedwig console to use hedwig metadata manager introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-250&quot; title=&quot;Need a ledger manager like interface to manage metadata operations in Hedwig&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BOOKKEEPER-250&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BOOKKEEPER-250&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-259&quot; title=&quot;Create a topic manager using versioned write for leader election&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BOOKKEEPER-259&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BOOKKEEPER-259&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13294277" author="hustlmsp" created="Wed, 13 Jun 2012 09:49:18 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;new patch similar as &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-203&quot; title=&quot;improve ledger manager interface to remove zookeeper dependency on metadata operations.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BOOKKEEPER-203&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BOOKKEEPER-203&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, to remove zookeeper integer version dependency.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13409291" author="hustlmsp" created="Mon, 9 Jul 2012 10:32:30 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;cancel patch until &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-250&quot; title=&quot;Need a ledger manager like interface to manage metadata operations in Hedwig&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BOOKKEEPER-250&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BOOKKEEPER-250&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-259&quot; title=&quot;Create a topic manager using versioned write for leader election&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BOOKKEEPER-259&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BOOKKEEPER-259&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; are finished.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13430377" author="hustlmsp" created="Tue, 7 Aug 2012 15:55:12 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;attach a new patch rebased to latest trunk after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-250&quot; title=&quot;Need a ledger manager like interface to manage metadata operations in Hedwig&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BOOKKEEPER-250&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BOOKKEEPER-250&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-259&quot; title=&quot;Create a topic manager using versioned write for leader election&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BOOKKEEPER-259&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BOOKKEEPER-259&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13436615" author="ikelly" created="Fri, 17 Aug 2012 09:56:18 +0100"  >&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Why are you returning ByteString from getTopics() source data is always String and the caller converts it back into String straight away anyhow.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;pressKeyToContinue should accept any key to continue, as there is only one possible continuation. I haven&apos;t run it, but from the look of it, it would require a Y&amp;lt;Return&amp;gt; to continue.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13436621" author="ikelly" created="Fri, 17 Aug 2012 10:06:30 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;actually, there&apos;s no clean way to read a character unbuffered from the console in java, so maybe pressKeyToContinue should be &quot;Press &amp;lt;Return&amp;gt; to continue&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13436635" author="hustlmsp" created="Fri, 17 Aug 2012 10:55:08 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; Why are you returning ByteString from getTopics() source data is always String and the caller converts it back into String straight away anyhow.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As all the hedwig uses ByteString for topic name, so we need to stick to the style.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; pressKeyToContinue should accept any key to continue, as there is only one possible continuation. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;it did accept any key to continue. just when user press &apos;y&apos; or &apos;Y&apos;, it continues showing next topic list. pressing other key would stop showing next topic list.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13436638" author="ikelly" created="Fri, 17 Aug 2012 11:05:26 +0100"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;As all the hedwig uses ByteString for topic name, so we need to stick to the style.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;it did accept any key to continue. just when user press &apos;y&apos; or &apos;Y&apos;, it continues showing next topic list. pressing other key would stop showing next topic list.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I think it would be better to have &quot;Press &amp;lt;Return&amp;gt; for more, or Q to cancel&quot;. As listing more will be the most common case, it would be good for it to be only one keystroke.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13436639" author="ikelly" created="Fri, 17 Aug 2012 11:07:30 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;In fact, you can use jline.Terminal if available to make both &amp;lt;Return&amp;gt; and Q as single keystroke.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13436720" author="hustlmsp" created="Fri, 17 Aug 2012 14:28:37 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;attach a new patch to address Ivan&apos;s comments, leverage ConsoleReader in console mode and Terminal in non-console mode.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13436739" author="ikelly" created="Fri, 17 Aug 2012 14:57:16 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed as r1374265. Thanks Sijie.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13436746" author="hudson" created="Fri, 17 Aug 2012 15:10:14 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in bookkeeper-trunk #653 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/bookkeeper-trunk/653/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/bookkeeper-trunk/653/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
